# Psoriasis — Master Findings Synthesis (RUO)

Journal-ready consolidation of the full real-data discovery campaign on psoriasis (MONDO:0005083). All findings from REAL public data (GEO expression/methylation/single-cell, Roadmap ChromHMM, ENCODE CTCF, LINCS L1000, UCSC hg19).

## Validated core finding

**The psoriatic epigenetic scar is a persistent, keratinocyte-specific hypermethylation-silencing of GATA-motif / CpG-island active differentiation enhancers.** It engages at the basal/progenitor cell state, tracks transcriptional silencing of the linked developmental genes (independent of promoter methylation), persists through phototherapy (72% of the lesional deviation does not recover; the silencing half replicates cross-cohort at p=2.6e-86), is epigenetically destabilized, varies across patients (scar-high/low axis), generalizes as a cross-cohort diagnostic biomarker (AUROC 0.84), and whose permanence is itself predictable (AUROC 0.82). The differentiation-silencing *target program* is shared with atopic dermatitis; the psoriasis-distinctive element is the persistence. Two honest self-corrections sharpened it: bivalent->enhancer (ChromHMM) and TFAP2A->GATA (sequence motif).

